    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-truffle-mushroom-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta</strong> for 7-9 min (10\u201312 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> pasta </strong>and return to the pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-truffle-mushroom-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pine nuts</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until lightly toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-truffle-mushroom-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>toasted pine nuts</strong> to a small bowl and set aside for later</p><p>Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and crumble your <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>roughly into the pan with your hands</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-truffle-mushroom-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> roasted garlic paste </strong>to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-truffle-mushroom-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Turn the heat down to medium-high and add your <strong>creamy single oat</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and<strong> </strong>the<strong> spinach </strong>to the pan</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the spinach has wilted and the sauce has slightly thickened</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>plant-based</strong> <strong>creamy mushroom sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-truffle-mushroom-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>to the <strong>plant-based</strong> <strong>creamy mushroom sauce</strong> and stir everything together \u2013 this is your <strong>plant-based creamy mushroom spaghetti</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-truffle-mushroom-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>plant-based creamy mushroom spaghetti </strong>with the <strong>toasted pine nuts</strong> sprinkled over the top</p><p>Drizzle over your <strong>truffle oil</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>plant-based</strong> <strong>creamy truffle mushroom spaghetti</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely over the spaghetti with scissors</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
